Simple Retrieve for dygraphs

Aaron Benz

02/18/2015

This is a simple script to pull data out of HBase and manipulate it so that you can plot it using dygraphs

library(rhbase)
library(magrittr)
library(data.table)
library(xts,warn.conflicts = F,quietly = T,verbose = F)
## 
## Attaching package: 'zoo'
## 
## The following objects are masked from 'package:base':

##     as.Date, as.Date.numeric
hb.init()
## <pointer: 0x2738960>
## attr(,"class")
## [1] "hb.client.connection"
airport <- "JFK"
variables <- c("rpm","speed")

Pull Data From HBase with hb.pull

data <- hb.pull("Test","test",start = airport,end = paste0(airport,"z"),columns = variables) %>%
    tidyr::separate(col = "rowkey", into = c("airport","day","vin"))

Merge Data-Sets Together

merge_em <- function(values){
    if(length(values)<=1) return(values[[1]])
    out <- values[[1]]
    for(i in 2:length(values)){
      out <- merge(out,values[[i]],all=T,by = "date_time")
    }
    out
}
  
data <- data[,list("rbinded" = list(merge_em(values))),by=c("vin","day","airport")] #data.table functionality

Format data.table as xts to use dyGraphs

data$date_time <- as.POSIXct.numeric(data$date_time,origin = "1970-01-01")
setnames(data,"date_time","timeDate")
data  <- xts(data[,2:length(data),with=F],data[[1]])

Graph it Using dygraphs

library(dygraphs)
data %>%
  dygraph(main = "A Dygraphs Chart!!!") %>% 
        dySeries(name = variables[1],axis = 'y') %>%
        dySeries(name = variables[2],axis = 'y2') %>%
        dyRangeSelector() %>%
        dyOptions(stepPlot = TRUE)
